article.headline: Texas-Pan American 79, Texas St. 77
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Brandon Provost made two free throws with 20 seconds left to give Texas-Pan American the go-ahead lead in a 79-77 victory over Texas State on Saturday night. Provost finished with 20 points for the Broncs (1-3) while teammate Jared Maree scored a game-high 21, including the final free throw with 2.9 seconds left. The teams traded the lead several times in the second half, with the Bobcats (3-1) going on a late 14-2 run to take a 77-76 advantage before Provost was fouled and sent to the free-throw line. The Broncs finished shooting 46 percent from the field, including making 9 of 22 3-point tries. The Bobcats shot 44 percent from the field but made just 2 of 11 from long distance. Eddie Rios and Nick Hinton led Texas State with 14 points each while Matt Staff added 12 and Brooks Ybarra 11.
